## When to use
Use this skill when you need real-time information on your disk I/O performance, free space, and other relevant metrics without having to manually run multiple commands.

## Approach
Create a custom shell function that combines the output from `df -h` for free space, `iostat` for I/O performance, and `smartctl -H` for health status of disks. Use `shell_exec` to execute these tools and combine their outputs into one comprehensive command.

## Example
```sh
function disk_status {
  echo "Disk Free Space:"
  shell_exec df -h | grep '^\/dev'
  echo "Disk I/O Performance:"
  shell_exec iostat -d 1 2
  echo "Disk Health Status:"
  for disk in $(shell_exec ls /dev/sd*); do
    shell_exec smartctl -H $disk
  done
}
```

## Pitfalls
Ensure that `iostat` and `smartctl` are installed on your system to avoid errors. Also, be aware of the time it takes for each command to run; some operations like `smartctl` can take longer depending on disk size and speed.